remarks: Two sets have the strict dominance relationship iff their cardinalities have the membership relationship.  Corollary 19.7(2) of [Eisenberg] p. 310.  (Contributed by NM, 22-Oct-2003.)  (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 30-Apr-2015.)
statement: cardsdom $p |- ( ( A e. V /\ B e. W ) -> ( ( card ` A ) e. ( card ` B ) <-> A ~< B ) ) $.
